  <entry>
    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:BlogPost//2012/01/01/Neacademia-version-2</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog/2012/01/01/Neacademia-version-2"/>
    <title>Neacademia version 2</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class='image'&gt;&lt;img src='https://old.rosettatype.com/blog/assets/Neacademia-version-2/Neacademia2_banner.png' title='' width='610'&gt;&lt;div class='imageDescription'&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Figure:&lt;/strong&gt; Neacademia version 2&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This updates includes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;many minor adjustments to Cyrillic lettershapes in order to further improve readability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;small caps for both Latin and Cyrillic in the upright (roman) version.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;small cap figures!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;some more alternate glyphs (Cyrillic alternate ф (ef) in italic is accessible via stylistic set 1).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;bug fixes and improvements to kerning and contextual alternates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please note that text originally set in some older version can reflow when reset in the updated version. Therefore, we recommend keeping backup copies of the old versions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the updated specimen to get a better idea of what has been changed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our thanks to Florian Hardwig and Maxim Zhukov for their insightful comments.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
