    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:BlogPost//2011/01/10/On-Non-Latin-Typefaces-book</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog/2011/01/10/On-Non-Latin-Typefaces-book"/>
    <title>On Non-Latin Typefaces</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;In 2007 a two-day conference about non-Latin typefaces was held at the Department of Typography &amp;amp; Graphics Communication, University of Reading. The accompanying exhibition was the first of its kind showing items from both institutions and some private collections. It included historical type specimens, technical drawings, sketches, photographs, all relating to non-Latin typefaces.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A 64-pages booklet about this exhibition, including essays by James Mosley and Fiona Ross, is available at the &lt;a href="http://stbridelibrary.bigcartel.com/product/non-latin-typefaces"&gt;St Bride’s eShop&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class='image'&gt;&lt;img src='https://old.rosettatype.com/blog/assets/Non-latin-typefaces/Non-latin-typefaces_1.jpg' title='' width='610'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class='image'&gt;&lt;img src='https://old.rosettatype.com/blog/assets/Non-latin-typefaces/Non-latin-typefaces_2.jpg' title='' width='610'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class='image'&gt;&lt;img src='https://old.rosettatype.com/blog/assets/Non-latin-typefaces/Non-latin-typefaces_3.jpg' title='' width='610'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
