    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2013/10/01/Three-winners-at-Granshan</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2013-10-01-three-winners-at-granshan"/>
    <title>Three winners at Granshan</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://granshan.org"&gt;Granshan&lt;/a&gt; is one of the most prestigious international competitions for type design, focussing on non-Latin scripts. We were proud to find that this year &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://rosettatype.com/Eskorte"&gt;Eskorte Arabic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; by Elena Schneider has won the first prize in the category of Arabic text typefaces, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.rosettatype.com/Skolar"&gt;Skolar Gujarati&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; by David Březina has won the second prize in the Indic text typefaces category, and best of all, &lt;strong&gt;Serendip Sinhala&lt;/strong&gt; by Rafael Saraiva, which is scheduled for a Rosetta release (it includes a brilliant Latin component btw), has won the first prize in the Indic category and also received the grand prize from Granshan! We are deeply honoured and humbled with this appreciation of our work.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
