    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2013/03/03/Reading-Exhibition-at-TypoDay</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2013-03-03-reading-exhibition-at-typoday"/>
    <title>Reading exhibition at TypoDay</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Material from the Non-Latin Type Collection of the University of Reading is on display at &lt;a href="http://typoday.in"&gt;TypoDay 2013&lt;/a&gt;. The exhibition, originally organised for ATypI Hong Kong, has now travelled to IIT Guwahati, the first time that drawings and documents from the Collection have been exhibited comprehensively in India. Co-curated by Fiona Ross and Vaibhav Singh, the display focuses on the various Indian scripts for which design- and production-related artefacts are preserved in the Collection. See also the &lt;a href="http://stbridelibrary.bigcartel.com/product/non-latin-scripts-from-metal-to-digital-type"&gt;remarkable book&lt;/a&gt; published to accompany the Hong Kong exhibition.&lt;/p&gt;
