  <entry>
    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2013/03/01/Huronia-release</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2013-03-01-huronia-release"/>
    <title>Huronia release</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;We have released &lt;a href="http://rosettatype.com/Huronia"&gt;Huronia&lt;/a&gt;, a new type family by &lt;a href="http://www.rosettatype.com/about&amp;amp;dsg=Mills"&gt;Ross Mills&lt;/a&gt;. It is a text face with flavour, suitable for extended reading. Huronia comprises fully-equipped Latin Pro (that is, it includes expert features: small caps, various figure sets, superiors, fractions) and Inuktitut syllabics. But these are just the first steps in a march towards supporting all of the native American languages in one type family. Read more about this handsome typeface on its dedicated page and in its PDF specimen.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
