    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2012/10/01/Burian-and-Scaglione-bid-adieu-to-Rosetta</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2012-10-01-burian-and-scaglione-bid-adieu-to-rosetta"/>
    <title>Burian and Scaglione bid adieu to Rosetta</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Life is made of ever so many partings welded together, as Charles Dickens put it. From 1 October 2012, Veronika Burian and José Scaglione have ceased to be partners at Rosetta Type Foundry. They have taken this step to strengthen their focus on the improvement of the TypeTogether retail library and tailored-fonts service. We wish them best of luck and extend our thanks for their generous help with the start-up of Rosetta Type Foundry. Rosetta will continue with its established team of talented designers, with David Březina as its director. It will carry on with its efforts in providing high-quality fonts for a variety of the world’s writing systems.&lt;/p&gt;
