  <entry>
    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2012/07/01/Innovation-series</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2012-07-01-innovation-series"/>
    <title>Innovation series</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Web &lt;a href="http://www.innovation-series.com/2012/06/06/font-face-attribute-future-of-user-experience"&gt;Innovation Series&lt;/a&gt; published an article about the problems of the Farsi typography on the web and the solutions we have provided for Voice of America. Some flattering testimonials from the design team included. Very happy to have happy customers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This font development is similar to the birth of Arial or Helvetica in English. “The results were stunning,” added Bahmani. (…) Bahmani tested NASSIM against the TAHOMA font and concluded that “the results demonstrated a 5x increase in reading speed.” (…) The new Persian VOA site (as shown in the graphic above) “was extremely well received and many users commented on how much better the site looks and how much more readable the text appears; there are no spacing, no kerning, and no proportion flaws,” added Bahmani.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These webfonts are available from &lt;a href="http://fontdeck.com/foundry/rosetta"&gt;Fontdeck&lt;/a&gt; (low-cost solution) and from &lt;a href="http://www.rosettatype.com/webfonts"&gt;our custom service&lt;/a&gt; (better quality, higher price).&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
