    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2012/06/01/Skolar-Devanagari-release</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2012-06-01-skolar-devanagari-release"/>
    <title>Skolar Devanagari release</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.rosettatype.com/Skolar"&gt;Skolar Devanagari&lt;/a&gt;, the latest addition to the Skolar family, is the result of a collaboration between David Březina and Vaibhav Singh. It has been designed as a companion to the Latin keeping the nuances and characteristics of the Devanagari script foremost while providing a complementary design for multi-script typography.  It is the first in a series of Indian typefaces we plan to release in the next 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
