  <entry>
    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2012/03/02/Webfonts</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2012-03-02-webfonts"/>
    <title>Webfonts</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;We are proud to announce that Rosetta fonts are now available to use as webfonts in two different flavours: webfont service and self-hosting. This is particularly important for Arabic web typography given the lack of high quality Arabic webfonts. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;For the convenience of those small businesses and startup sites looking to have high quality fonts for a limited budget we have partnered up with the webfont service bureau &lt;a href="http://fontdeck.com/foundry/rosetta"&gt;Fontdeck&lt;/a&gt;. Their solution requires no special coding skills, and they offer a very fast and reliable &lt;a href="http://fontdeck.com/about/speed"&gt;infrastructure&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;For larger companies that deal with several million pageviews per month, and have more demanding needs in terms of bandwidth and infrastructure we also offer our webfonts specially customised for self hosting.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Learn more about these &lt;a href="http://www.rosettatype.com/webfonts"&gt;on our webfonts page&lt;/a&gt; or simply contact us.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
