    <id>tag:old.rosettatype.com,2005:NewsPost//2011/01/01/Nassim-on-BBC-Arabic</id>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://old.rosettatype.com/blog#newsDetailSection-2011-01-01-nassim-on-bbc-arabic"/>
    <title>Nassim on BBC Arabic</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Following the redesign of the mother-page of the BBC News, the BBC Arabic launched their new website. It is probably one of the first, and certainly the biggest site yet to use webfonts – Arabic webfonts that is. It uses a custom version of our upcoming Nassim by Titus Nemeth. The typeface was painstakingly optimised for screen and for web. &lt;/p&gt;
</content>
